ong-The-Living-Legend/overview|title=King Kong: The Living Legend \u2013 TV Special|publisher=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n*1987: ''[[The Little Troll Prince|The Little Troll Prince: A Christmas Parable]]'' as King Ulvik a.k.a. Left Head (voice)\n*1988: ''[[Moon over Parador]]'' as Ralph\n*1988: ''[[Completely Mental Misadventures of Ed Grimley|The Completely Mental Misadventures of Ed Grimley]]'' as Roger Gustav and Mr. Freebus (voice)\n*1990: ''[[Tiny Toon Adventures]]'' as Sappy Stanley (voice, in episode \"Who Bopped Bugs Bunny\")\n*1991: ''[[Rick Moranis in Gravedale High]]'' as Coach Cadaver\n*1991: ''[[Little Dracula]]'' as Igor, Granny\n*1991: ''[[The Story of Holly and Ivy|The Wish that Changed Christmas]]'' (voice on TV special)\n*1992: ''Tiny Toon Adventures: How I Spent My Vacation'' as Wade Pig / Superman (voice)\n*1992: ''[[Davis Rules]]'' as Gunny Davis\n*1992: ''[[Frosty Returns]]'' ([[narrator]])\n*1992: ''Spaced Out!''; host (also [[executive producer]]) {{small|(features comics such as [[Bonnie Hunt]], [[Carrot Top]] and others)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000YC15A8|publisher=Amazon.com|title=Spaced Out: Jonathan Winters}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://tv.yahoo.com/shows/jonathan-winters-spaced-out/|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130630173045/http://tv.yahoo.com/shows/jonathan-winters-spaced-out/|url-status=dead|archive-date=2013-06-30|title=Jonathan Winters: Spaced Out|publisher=Yahoo! TV}}</ref>\n*1993: ''[[The Thief and the Cobbler]]'' under the theatrical name ''[[The Thief and the Cobbler#Changes made in Arabian Knight (1995, Miramax)|Arabian Knight]]'' as The Thief (Miramax version) (voice)\n*1993: ''Precious Moments: Timmy's Special Delivery'' (voice; Christmas movie)\n*1994: ''Christopher and Holly a.k.a. The Bears Who Saved Christmas'' as Charlie the Compass (voice)\n*1994: ''[[Yogi the Easter Bear]]'' as [[List of Yogi Bear characters#Ranger Mortimer|Ranger Mortimer]] (voice)\n*1994: ''[[The Flintstones (film)|The Flints