k Paar]], [[Louis Nye]] and others)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00027EK8O |publisher=Amazon.com|title=Jonathan Winters: The Lost Episodes}}</ref>\n*1986: ''Say Yes'' (VHS)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/6302874505|publisher=Amazon.com|title= Say Yes (VHS)}}</ref>\n*1986: ''Jonathan Winters: Madman of Comedy'' (VHS)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00005O5IY|publisher=Amazon.com|title= Jonathan Winters:Madman of Comedy (VHS)}}</ref>\n*1987: ''On The Ledge'' (VHS)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/630178510X|publisher=Amazon.com|title=Jonathan Winters \u2013 On The Ledge (VHS)}}</ref>\n*1991: ''Johnny Carson (with Jonathan Winters and Robin Williams)'' <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qzv6EhE7Cbo |title=Robin Williams on Carson w/ Jonathan Winters 1991 |publisher=[[YouTube]] |date= |accessdate=2020-03-18}}</ref> (On Clarence Thomas Supreme Court nomination)\n*1995: ''Jonathan Winters: Gone Fish'n'' (VHS/[[DVD]]) {{small|Winters also credited as [[editing|editor]]}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jonathanwinters.com/books.html|title=Jonathan Winters: Books|publisher=jonathanwinters.com}}</ref>\n*2000: ''The Unknown Jonathan Winters: On the Loose'' (VHS/DVD)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00004U0FQ|publisher=Amazon.com|title=The Unknown Jonathan Winters: On the Loose}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00004U0T7 |publisher=Amazon.com|title= The Unknown Jonathan Winters \u2013 On the Loose (VHS)}}</ref>\n*2005: ''Jonathan Winters: Rare and Riotous'' (VHS/DVD)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0007L86L2|publisher=Amazon.com|title=Jonathan Winters: Rare and Riotous}}</ref>\n*2007: ''Certifiably Jonathan'' (DVD) {{small|(features [[Howie Mandel]], [[Tim Conway]], [[Jimmy Kimmel]], [[Sarah Silverman]] and others)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B006WDHEEE|publisher=Amazon.com|title=Certifiably Jonathan}}</ref>\n*2011: ''Jonathan Winters: Birth of a Genius'' (DVD)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B002MYDA6I|publisher=Amazon.com|title=Jonathan Winters: Birth of a Genius}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n* ''Mouse Breath, Conformity and Other Social Ills'' (1965) ([[hardcover]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0007EI6I2|publisher=Amazon.com|title=Mouse breath, conformity, and other social ills}}</ref>\n* ''Winters' Tales: Stories and Observations for the Unusual'' ([[First edition|1st edition]] 1987)/ (2nd edition 1993) / (3rd edition 2001) ([[paperback]])<ref name=\"GoodReads1\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B001ZTXV5G|title=Winters' Tales: Jonathan Winters: 9780394759784|publisher=Amazon.com}}</ref>\n* ''Hang-Ups: Paintings by Jonathan Winters'' (1st edition 1988) (hardcover)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/0394570243|publisher=Amazon.com|title=Hang-Ups: Paintings by Jonathan Winters (9780394570242)}}</ref>\n* ''Jonathan Winters: After The Beep '' (1989) (paperback)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/0399515356|title=Jonathan Winters: After The Beep: Jim B. Smith: 9780399515354|publisher=Amazon.com}}</ref>\n* ''Jonathan Winters' [[A Christmas Carol]]'' (first aired on [[NPR]] in 1990,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/product-description/1598875329|publisher=Amazon.com|title=A Christmas Carol (9781598875324): Charles Dickens, Mimi Kennedy, Jonathan Winters, Laurence Olivier, Susan Stamberg}}</ref> published on CD ([[audiobook]]) September 5, 2007) <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/A-Christmas-Carol-Charles-Dickens/dp/1598875329|publisher=Amazon.com|title=Publisher: HighBridge Company; Unabridged, Fully Dramatized; 1 hour on 1 CD edition (September 5, 2007) ISBN 1598875329}}</ref>\n* ''Maude Frickert Tells All'' (2010) (hardcover)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15235334-maude-frickert-tells-all|title=Maude Frickert Tells All by Jonathan Winters |publisher=goodreads.com}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Porta