cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000YC15A8|publisher=Amazon.com|title=Spaced Out: Jonathan Winters}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://tv.yahoo.com/shows/jonathan-winters-spaced-out/|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130630173045/http://tv.yahoo.com/shows/jonathan-winters-spaced-out/|url-status=dead|archive-date=2013-06-30|title=Jonathan Winters: Spaced Out|publisher=Yahoo! TV}}</ref>\n*1993: ''[[The Thief and the Cobbler]]'' under the theatrical name ''[[The Thief and the Cobbler#Changes made in Arabian Knight (1995, Miramax)|Arabian Knight]]'' as The Thief (Miramax version) (voice)\n*1993: ''Precious Moments: Timmy's Special Delivery'' (voice; Christmas movie)\n*1994: ''Christopher and Holly a.k.a. The Bears Who Saved Christmas'' as Charlie the Compass (voice)\n*1994: ''[[Yogi the Easter Bear]]'' as [[List of Yogi Bear characters#Ranger Mortimer|Ranger Mortimer]] (voice)\n*1994: ''[[The Flintstones (film)|The Flintstones]]'' as Grizzled Man\n*1994: ''[[The Shadow (1994 film)|The Shadow]]'' as Wainwright Cranston\n*2000: ''[[The Adventures of Rocky and Bullwinkle (film)|The Adventures of Rocky and Bullwinkle]]'' as Whoppa Chopper Pilot / Ohio Cop with Bullhorn / Jeb<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/adventures_of_rocky_and_bullwinkle/|title=The Adventures of Rocky & Bullwinkle|publisher=Rotten Tomatoes}}</ref>\n*2003: ''[[Swing (2003 film)|Swing]]'' as Uncle Bill\n*2004: ''[[Comic Book: The Movie]]'' as Wally (Army Buddy #2)\n*2004: ''Tell Them Who You Are'' ([[documentary film]]) as Himself<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/celebrity/jonathan_winters/|title=Jonathan Winters |publisher= Rotten Tomatoes}}</ref>\n*2006: ''[[Cattle Call|National Lampoon's Cattle Call]]'' as Thomas the Studio Tour Guide\n*2007: ''Certifiably Jonathan''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.certifiablyjonathan.com |title=Jonathan Winters Film |publisher=Certifiably Jonathan |date= |accessdate=April 5, 2011}}</ref> ([[Feel Good Film Festival#Celebrities honored|honored celebrity at FGFF]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/certifiably-jonathan/|title=Certifiably Jonathan|publisher= Rotten Tomatoes}}</ref>\n*2011: ''[[The Smurfs (film)|The Smurfs]]'' as [[Papa Smurf]] (voice)\n*2013: ''[[The Smurfs 2]]'' as Papa Smurf (voice) (released posthumously)\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Short films===\n*1968: ''The Early Birds'' (writer and voices)<ref name=\"HistoryForSale\" />\n*1974: ''Sonic Boom'' (performer)\n*2000: ''[[Edwurd Fudwupper Fibbed Big]]'' (voice actor)\n*2002: ''[[Santa vs. the Snowman 3D]]'' (voice of [[Santa Claus]])\n\n==Discography==\n{{Div col|colwidth=30em}}\n*1960: ''Down to Earth''\n*1960: ''[[The Wonderful World of Jonathan Winters]]'' (reissued in 2003)\n*1961: ''Here's Jonathan''\n*1962: ''Another Day, Another World''\n*1962: ''Humor Seen through the Eyes of Jonathan Winters''\n*1964: ''Whistle Stopping with Jonathan Winters''\n*1966: ''Movies Are Better Than Ever''\n*1969: ''Jonathan Winters\u2026 Wings it!''\n*1969: ''Stuff 'n Nonsense''\n*1973: ''Jonathan Winters and Friends Laugh ... Live''\n*1975: ''[[The Little Prince]]'' (featured in [[List of The Little Prince adaptations#Vinyl record|an adaptation]] with [[Richard Burton]])\n*1987: ''Jonathan Winters Answers Your Telephone''\n*1988: ''Finally Captured''\n*1988: ''Winter's Tales'' (audio book)\n*1989: ''Jonathan Winters Tells The Story Of Peter And The Wolf''\n*1989: ''Hang-Ups Cal'90''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/13304582-hang-ups-cal-90|title=Hang-Ups Cal'90 by Jonathan Winters |publisher=goodreads.com}}</ref>\n*1990: ''Into the '90s''\n*1992: ''Jonathan Winters is Terminator 3''\n*1992: ''Paul Bunyan''\n*1993: ''Best of Jonathan Winters'' ([[Compact Cassette|audio cassette]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/1558008411|title=Best of Jonathan Winters: Jonathan Winters: 9781558008410|publisher=Amazon.com}}</ref>\n*1995: ''Crank(y) Calls''\n*1995: ''[[The Thief and the Cobbler]]'' a.k.a. ''[[