orewords describing the science and technology that appears in the books.\n\n== Books ==\nThe series was not numbered. This chronological list identifies the artists who usually illustrated the dustjackets only (\"cover\"), occasionally illustrated the novels too (\"cover and interior illus.\").\n\n* ''[[Earthbound (book)|Earthbound]]'' by [[Milton Lesser]], cover by Peter Poulton (1952)\n* ''[[Find the Feathered Serpent]]'', [[Evan Hunter]], cover [[Henry Sharp (artist)|Henry Sharp]] (1952)\n* ''[[Five Against Venus]]'', [[Robert S. Richardson|Philip Latham]] (Robert S. Richardson), cover [[Virgil Finlay]] (1952)\n* ''[[Islands in the Sky]]'', [[Arthur C. Clarke]], cover [[Alex Schomburg]] (1952)\n* ''[[Marooned on Mars]]'', [[Lester del Rey]], cover  [[Paul Orban]] (1952)\n* ''[[Mists of Dawn]]'', [[Chad Oliver]], cover  Alex Schomburg (1952)\n* ''[[Rocket Jockey (novel)|Rocket Jockey]]'', [[Philip St. John]] (Lester del Rey), cover  Alex Schomburg (1952)\n* ''[[Son of the Stars]]'', [[Raymond F. Jones]], cover  Alex Schomburg (1952) \u2013 Clonar, book 1\n* ''[[Sons of the Ocean Deeps]]'', [[Bryce Walton]], cover  Paul Orban (1952)\n* ''[[Vault of the Ages]]'', [[Poul Anderson]], cover  Paul Orban (1952)\n* ''[[Attack from Atlantis]]'', Lester del Rey, cover  [[Kenneth S. Fagg]] (1953)\n* ''[[Battle on Mercury]]'', [[Erik Van Lhin]] (Lester del Rey), cover  Kenneth S. Fagg (1953)\n* ''[[Danger: Dinosaurs!]]'', [[Richard Marsten]] (Evan Hunter), cover  Alex Schomburg (1953)\n* ''[[Missing Men of Saturn]]'', Philip Latham, cover  Alex Schomburg (1953)\n* ''[[The Mysterious Planet (book)|The Mysterious Planet]]'', [[Lester del Rey|Kenneth Wright]] (Lester del Rey), cover  Alex Schomburg (1953)\n* ''[[Mystery of the Third Mine]]'', [[Robert W. Lowndes]], cover  Kenneth S. Fagg (1953)\n* ''[[Planet of Light]]'', Raymond F. Jones, cover  Alex Schomburg (1953) \u2013 Clonar, book 2\n* ''[[Rocket to Luna]]'', Richard Marsten (Evan Hunter), cover by Alex Schomburg (1953)\n* ''[[The Star Seekers]]'', [[Milton Lesser]], cover  [[Paul Calle]] (1953)\n* ''[[Vandals of the Void]]'', [[Jack Vance]], cover  Alex Schomburg (1953)\n* ''[[Rockets to Nowhere]]'', Philip St. John (Lester Del Rey), cover  Alex Schomburg (1954)\n* ''[[The Secret of Saturn's Rings]]'', [[Donald A. Wollheim]], cover  Alex Schomburg (1954)\n* ''[[Step to the Stars]]'', Lester del Rey, cover  Alex Schomburg (1954) \u2013 Jim Stanley, book 1\n* ''[[Trouble on Titan]]'', [[Alan E. Nourse]], cover  Alex Schomburg (1954)\n* ''[[The World at Bay]]'', [[Paul Capon]], cover  Alex Schomburg  (1954)\n* ''[[The Year After Tomorrow]]'', eds. Lester del Rey, Cecile Matschat, and Carl Carmer, cover and interior illus. [[Mel Hunter]] (1954) \u2013 anthology of nine short stories\n* ''[[The Ant Men]]'', [[Eric North]], cover  [[Paul Blaisdell]] (1955)\n* ''[[The Secret of the Martian Moons]]'', [[Donald A. Wollheim]], cover  Alex Schomburg (1955)\n* ''[[The Lost Planet (Paul Dallas novel)|The Lost Planet]]'', [[Paul Dallas]], cover  Alex Schomburg (1956)\n* ''[[Mission to the Moon]]'', Lester del Rey, cover  Alex Schomburg  (1956) \u2013 Jim Stanley, book 2\n* ''[[Rockets Through Space]]'', Lester del Rey, cover and interior illus. [[James Heugh]] (1957) \u2013 Special Companion Book (nonfiction)\n* ''[[The Year When Stardust Fell]]'', Raymond F. Jones, cover James Heugh (1958)\n* ''[[The Secret of the Ninth Planet]]'', Donald A. Wollheim, cover James Heugh (1959)\n* ''[[The Star Conquerors]]'', [[Ben Bova]], cover Mel Hunter (1959)\n* ''[[Stadium Beyond the Stars]]'', Milton Lesser, cover Mel Hunter (1960)\n* ''[[Moon of Mutiny]]'', Lester del Rey, cover [[Ed Emshwiller]] (1961) \u2013 Jim Stanley, book 3\n* ''[[Spacemen, Go Home]]'', Milton Lesser, cover Ed Emshwiller (1961)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist |25em}}\n\n==External links==\n\n* [http://www.isfdb.org/cgi-bin/pubseries.cgi?790 Winston Science Fiction] at the [[Internet Speculative Fiction Database]] <!-- as of 2015-12-20, list of 36 not include the one anthology -->\n\n[[Category:American speculative fiction publishers]]\n[[Category:American science fiction]]\n[[Category:Science fiction book series]]\n[[Category:Young adult novel series]] <!-- publisher series without any continuity in content -->\n[[Category:Children's science fiction novels]]\n[[Category:Science fiction publishers]] <!-- strictly the publisher is John C. Winston Co. -->\n", "name_user": "JHunterJ", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: 1910-1941 \u2192 1910  to 1941", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Winston_Science_Fiction"}
{"title_page": "Athletics at the 1976 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's discus throw", "text_new": "{{Infobox Olympic event\n|event = Men's discus throw\n|games = 1976 Summer\n|image =\n|caption =\n|date = {{Date|1976-7-24}} (qualifications)<br />{{Date|1976-7-25}} (final)\n|venue = [[Olympic Stadium (Montreal)|Olympic Stadium]]\n|competitors = 30\n|nations = 20\n|win_label = Winning distance\n|win_value = 67.50\n|longnames = yes\n|gold = [[Mac Wilkins]]\n|goldNOC = USA\n|silver = [[Wolfgang Schmidt]]\n|silverNOC = GDR\n|bronze = [[John Powell (athlete)|John Powell]]\n|bronzeNOC = USA\n|prev = [[Athletics at the 1972 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's discus throw|1972]]\n|next = [[Athletics at the 1980 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's discus throw|1980]]\n}}\n{{AthleticsAt1976SummerOlympics}}\nThe '''[[Discus throw|Men's Discus Throw]]''' event at the '''[[Athletics at the 1976 Summer Olympics|1976 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Montreal|Montreal, Quebec]], [[Canada]] had an entry list of 30 competitors, with two qualifying groups (30 jumpers) before the final (15) took place on Sunday July 25, 1976. The top twelve and ties, and all those reaching 60.00 metres advanced to the final. The qualification round was held in Saturday July 24, 1976.<ref name=\"SR\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1976/ATH/mens-discus-throw.html |title=Athletics at the 1976 Montreal Summer Games: Men's Discus Throw |accessdate=13 January 2018 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>\n\n==Medalists==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"35%\"\n|- \n|{{OlympicGoldMedalist|[[Mac Wilkins]]|USA|1976 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicSilverMedalist|[[Wolfgang Schmidt]]|GDR|1976 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicBronzeMedalist|[[John Powell (athlete)|John Powell]]|USA|1976 Summer}}\n|}\n\n==Abbreviations==\n*''All results shown are in metres''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"35%\"\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"ccffcc\"| '''Q''' || automatic qualification\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"ddffdd\"| '''q''' || qualification by rank\n|-\n|'''DNS''' || did not start\n|-\n|'''NM''' || no mark\n|-\n|'''OR''' || olympic record\n|-\n|'''WR''' || world record\n|-\n|'''AR''' || area record\n|-\n|'''NR''' || national record\n|-\n|'''PB''' || personal best\n|-\n|'''SB''' || season best\n|}\n\n==Records==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"95%\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"5\"|Standing records prior to the 1976 Summer Olympics\n|-\n| [[List of world records in athletics|World Record]] || {{flagathlete|[[Mac Wilkins]]|USA}} || '''70.86 m '''|| May 1, 1976 || {{flagicon|USA}} [[San Jose, California]], [[United States]]\n|-\n| [[List of Olympic records in athletics|Olympic Record]] || {{flagathlete|[[Al Oerter]]|USA}} || '''64.78 m '''|| October 15, 1968 || {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]] \n|}\n\n==Qualification==\n\n===Group A===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"95%\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Rank\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Overall\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Athlete\n!colspan=\"3\"|Attempts\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Result\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Note\n|-\n!1\n!2\n!3\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n| 1 || 1||align=left| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Mac Wilkins]]|USA|1976 Summer}}\n|68.28\n|align=\"center\" |&mdash;\n|align=\"center\" |&mdash;\n|align=\"center\" |'''68.28 m'''||'''OR'''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n| 2 || 2||align=left| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Velko Velev]]|BUL|1976 Summer}}\n|63.54\n|align=\"center\" |&mdash;\n|align=\"center\" |&mdash;\n|align=\"center\" |'''63.54 m'''||\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n| 3 || 3||align=left| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Wolfgang Schmidt]]|GDR|1976 Summer}}\n|63.14\n|align=\"center\" |&mdash;\n|align=\"center\" |&mdash;\n|align=\"center\" |'''63.14 m'''||\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n| 4 || 5||align=left| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Pentti Kahma]]|FIN|1976 Summer}}\n|62.10\n|align=\"center\" |&mdash;\n|align=\"center\" |&mdash; \n|align=\"center\" |'''62.