{"title_page": "Casio Loopy", "text_new": "{{short description|Video game console}}\n{{more citations needed|date=December 2018}}\n{{ infobox CVG system\n| logo         = [[Image:Casio-loopy-logo.png|100px]]\n| image        = [[File:Casio-Loopy-Console-Set.jpg|300px]]\n| manufacturer = [[Casio]]\n| type         = [[Home video game console]]\n| lifespan     = {{vgrelease|JP|October 19, 1995 - December 1998}}\n| generation   = [[History of video game consoles (fifth generation)|Fifth generation]]\n| CPU          = [[32-bit]] [[RISC]] [[SuperH#Models|SH-1]] (SH7021)\n| media        = [[ROM cartridge|Cartridge]]\n| controllers  = D-pad, [[Mouse (computing)|Mouse]]\n| predecessor  = [[PV-1000]]\n}}\n\nThe {{nihongo|'''Casio Loopy'''|\u30eb\u30fc\u30d4\u30fc|R\u016bp\u012b|lead=yes}}, subtitled ''My Seal Computer SV-100'', is a [[32-bit]] [[home video game console]]. Released exclusively in [[Video gaming in Japan|Japan]] in October 1995, it was unique in that the marketing for it was completely targeted to [[Women and video games|female gamers]].\n\nThe Loopy includes a built-in thermal color [[Computer printer|printer]] that can be used to create [[sticker]]s from game screenshots. An optional accessory, called {{nihongo|''Magical Shop''|\u30de\u30b8\u30ab\u30eb\u30b7\u30e7\u30c3\u30d7|Majikaru Shoppu}}, is a video capture device to obtain images from [[Videocassette recorder|VCRs]] and [[DVD player]]s. Users may add text to these images and make stickers. Including Magical Shop's own built-in software, the Loopy library contains 10 games. The Loopy features one controller port for use with a standard [[game controller]] or with a mouse which was sold separately. Developer [[Kenji Terada]] worked on ''Loopy Town no Oheya ga Hoshii!''.\n\nCasio ceased production of the console in December 1998, with software development ending in November 1996.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-07-15-in-the-loopy-the-story-of-casios-crazy-90s-console|title=In the Loopy: the story of Casio's crazy 90s console|first=Lewis|last=Packwood|date=July 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Games==\n*{{nihongo|''Anime Land''|\u3042\u306b\u3081\u3089\u3093\u3069|Animerando}}\n*{{nihongo|''Bow-wow Puppy Love Story''|\u308f\u3093\u308f\u3093\u611b\u60c5\u7269\u8a9e|Wanwan Aij\u014d Monogatari}}\n*{{nihongo|''Dream Change: Kokin-chan's Fashion Party''|\u30c9\u30ea\u30fc\u30e0\u30c1\u30a7\u30f3\u30b8 \u5c0f\u91d1\u3061\u3083\u3093\u306e\u30d5\u30a1\u30c3\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u30d1\u30fc\u30c6\u30a3\u30fc|Dor\u012bmuchenji Kokinchanno Fasshonp\u0101t\u012b}}\n*{{nihongo|''HARIHARI Seal Paradise''|HARIHARI\u30b7\u30fc\u30eb\u30d1\u30e9\u30c0\u30a4\u30b9|HARIHARI Sh\u012bru Paradaisu}}\n*{{nihongo|''I Want a Room in Loopy Town!''|\u30eb\u30fc\u30d4\u30fc\u30bf\u30a6\u30f3\u306e\u304a\u3078\u3084\u304c\u307b\u3057\u3044!|R\u016bp\u012b Taun no O-heya ga Hoshii!}}\n*{{nihongo|''Little Romance''|\u30ea\u30c8\u30eb\u30ed\u30de\u30f3\u30b9|Ritoru Romansu}}\n*{{nihongo|''Lupiton's Wonder Palette''|\u30eb\u30d4\u30c8\u30f3\u306e\u30ef\u30f3\u30c0\u30fc\u30d1\u30ec\u30c3\u30c8|Rupiton no Wand\u0101paretto}}\n*{{nihongo|''Chakra-kun's Charm Paradise''|\u30c1\u30e3\u30af\u30e9\u304f\u3093\u306e\u304a\u307e\u3058\u306a\u3044\u30d1\u30e9\u30c0\u30a4\u30b9|Chakurakun no Omajinai Paradaisu}}\n*{{nihongo|''Caricature Artist''|\u4f3c\u9854\u7d75\u30a2\u30fc\u30c6\u30a3\u30b9\u30c8|Nigaoe \u0100tisuto}}\n*{{nihongo|''PC Collection''|\u30d1\u30bd\u30b3\u30f3\u30fb\u30b3\u30ec\u30af\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3|Pasokon Korekushon}}\n\nThe games ''PC Collection'' and ''Lupiton's Wonder Palette'' were both packaged either as stand-alone or bundled with the mouse.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://ultimateconsoledatabase.com/golden/casio_loopy.htm Casio Loopy on UltimateConsoleDatabase.com]\n*[http://www.old-computers.com/MUSEUM/computer.asp?c=774&st=2 Casio Loopy on old-computers.com]\n*[http://www.uk.playright.dk/raretitel.php?id=29220 Casio Loopy on playright.dk]\n*[http://www.rfgeneration.com/news/classic-gaming/System-Overview-Casio-Loopy-My-Seal-Computer-362.php Casio Loopy on rfgeneration.com]\n*[https://archive.today/20130905030011/http://loopy.femicom.org/ FEMICOM Museum's Casio Loopy Collection]\n*[http://videogamekraken.com/casio-loopy Video Game Kraken - Loopy]\n\n{{Fifth generation game consoles}}\n{{Home video game consoles}}\n{{Casio}}\n\n[[Category:Home video game consoles]]\n[[Category:Fifth-generation video game consoles]]\n[[Category:Japan-only video game hardware]]\n[[Category:Casio brands|Loopy]]\n[[Category:Products introduced in 1995]]\n[[Category:Women and video games]]\n\n{{videogame-hardware-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Video game console}}\n{{more citations needed|date=December 2018}}\n{{ infobox CVG system\n| logo         = [[Image:Casio-loopy-logo.png|100px]]\n| image        = [[File:Casio-Loopy-Console-Set.jpg|300px]]\n| manufacturer = [[Casio]]\n| type         = [[Home video game console]]\n| lifespan     = {{vgrelease|JP|October 19, 1995 - December 1998}}\n| generation   = [[History of video game consoles (fifth generation)|Fifth generation]]\n| CPU          = [[32-bit]] [[RISC]] [[SuperH#Models|SH-1]] (SH7021)\n| media        = [[ROM cartridge|Cartridge]]\n| controllers  = D-pad, [[Mouse (computing)|Mouse]]\n| predecessor  = [[PV-1000]]\n}}\n\nThe {{nihongo|'''Casio Loopy'''|\u30eb\u30fc\u30d4\u30fc|R\u016bp\u012b|lead=yes}}, subtitled ''My Seal Computer SV-100'', is a [[32-bit]] [[home video game console]]. Released exclusively in [[Video gaming in Japan|Japan]] in October 1995, it was unique in that the marketing for it was completely targeted to [[Women and video games|female gamers]].\n\nThe Loopy includes a built-in thermal color [[Computer printer|printer]] that can be used to create [[sticker]]s from game screenshots. An optional accessory, called {{nihongo|''Magical Shop''|\u30de\u30b8\u30ab\u30eb\u30b7\u30e7\u30c3\u30d7|Majikaru Shoppu}}, is a video capture device to obtain images from [[Videocassette recorder|VCRs]] and [[DVD player]]s. Users may add text to these images and make stickers. Including Magical Shop's own built-in software, the Loopy library contains 11 games. The Loopy features one controller port for use with a standard [[game controller]] or with a mouse which was sold separately. Developer [[Kenji Terada]] worked on ''Loopy Town no Oheya ga Hoshii!''.\n\nCasio ceased production of the console in December 1998, with software development ending in November 1996.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-07-15-in-the-loopy-the-story-of-casios-crazy-90s-console|title=In the Loopy: the story of Casio's crazy 90s console|first=Lewis|last=Packwood|date=July 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Games==\n*{{nihongo|''Anime Land''|\u3042\u306b\u3081\u3089\u3093\u3069|Animerando}}\n*{{nihongo|''Bow-wow Puppy Love Story''|\u308f\u3093\u308f\u3093\u611b\u60c5\u7269\u8a9e|Wanwan Aij\u014d Monogatari}}\n*{{nihongo|''Dream Change: Kokin-chan's Fashion Party''|\u30c9\u30ea\u30fc\u30e0\u30c1\u30a7\u30f3\u30b8 \u5c0f\u91d1\u3061\u3083\u3093\u306e\u30d5\u30a1\u30c3\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u30d1\u30fc\u30c6\u30a3\u30fc|Dor\u012bmuchenji Kokinchanno Fasshonp\u0101t\u012b}}\n*{{nihongo|''HARIHARI Seal Paradise''|HARIHARI\u30b7\u30fc\u30eb\u30d1\u30e9\u30c0\u30a4\u30b9|HARIHARI Sh\u012bru Paradaisu}}\n*{{nihongo|''I Want a Room in Loopy Town!''|\u30eb\u30fc\u30d4\u30fc\u30bf\u30a6\u30f3\u306e\u304a\u3078\u3084\u304c\u307b\u3057\u3044!|R\u016bp\u012b Taun no O-heya ga Hoshii!}}\n*{{nihongo|''Little Romance''|\u30ea\u30c8\u30eb\u30ed\u30de\u30f3\u30b9|Ritoru Romansu}}\n*{{nihongo|''Lupiton's Wonder Palette''|\u30eb\u30d4\u30c8\u30f3\u306e\u30ef\u30f3\u30c0\u30fc\u30d1\u30ec\u30c3\u30c8|Rupiton no Wand\u0101paretto}}\n*{{nihongo|''Chakra-kun's Charm Paradise''|\u30c1\u30e3\u30af\u30e9\u304f\u3093\u306e\u304a\u307e\u3058\u306a\u3044\u30d1\u30e9\u30c0\u30a4\u30b9|Chakurakun no Omajinai Paradaisu}}\n*{{nihongo|''Caricature Artist''|\u4f3c\u9854\u7d75\u30a2\u30fc\u30c6\u30a3\u30b9\u30c8|Nigaoe \u0100tisuto}}\n*{{nihongo|''PC Collection''|\u30d1\u30bd\u30b3\u30f3\u30fb\u30b3\u30ec\u30af\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3|Pasokon Korekushon}}\n\nThe games ''PC Collection'' and ''Lupiton's Wonder Palette'' were both packaged either as stand-alone or bundled with the mouse.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://ultimateconsoledatabase.com/golden/casio_loopy.htm Casio Loopy on UltimateConsoleDatabase.com]\n*[http://www.old-computers.com/MUSEUM/computer.asp?c=774&st=2 Casio Loopy on old-computers.com]\n*[http://www.uk.playright.dk/raretitel.php?id=29220 Casio Loopy on playright.dk]\n*[http://www.rfgeneration.com/news/classic-gaming/System-Overview-Casio-Loopy-My-Seal-Computer-362.php Casio Loopy on rfgeneration.com]\n*[https://archive.today/20130905030011/http://loopy.femicom.org/ FEMICOM Museum's Casio Loopy Collection]\n*[http://videogamekraken.com/casio-loopy Video Game Kraken - Loopy]\n\n{{Fifth generation game consoles}}\n{{Home video game consoles}}\n{{Casio}}\n\n[[Category:Home video game consoles]]\n[[Category:Fifth-generation video game consoles]]\n[[Category:Japan-only video game hardware]]\n[[Category:Casio brands|Loopy]]\n[[Category:Products introduced in 1995]]\n[[Category:Women and video games]]\n\n{{videogame-hardware-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ajoh198", "label": "safe", "comment": "Only ten games are listed below, in addition the primary source for this article (https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-07-15-in-the-loopy-the-story-of-casios-crazy-90s-console) specifically says that only ten games were released.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Casio_Loopy"}
{"title_page": "List of translations of the Paschal greeting", "text_new": "{{cleanup lang|date=May 2019}}\n[[File:Resurrection_(24).jpg|right|thumb|The [[w: Resurrection of Jesus Christ|resurrection of Jesus Christ]] from the [[dead]], described in the [[New Testament]] as having occurred on the third day after [[Crucifixion of Jesus|his crucifixion]] at [[Calvary]].]]\n{{Eastern Orthodox sidebar|expanded=worship}}\nThis article lists translations of the Christian [[Paschal greeting]] in various languages.\n\n==The Paschal Greeting in various languages==\n\n===[[Indo-European languages]]===\n*[[Greek language|Greek]] \u2013 \u03a7\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u1f78\u03c2 \u1f00\u03bd\u03ad\u03c3\u03c4\u03b7! \u1f08\u03bb\u03b7\u03b8\u1ff6\u03c2 \u1f00\u03bd\u03ad\u03c3\u03c4\u03b7! (Khrist\u00f3s An\u00e9sti! Alith\u00f3s An\u00e9sti!)\n*[[Slavic languages]]\n**[[Church Slavonic language|Church Slavonic]] \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u0457\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0301\u0441\u044a \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0301\u0441\u0435! \u0412\u043e\u0438\u0301\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\ua64b \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0301\u0441\u0435! (Xrist\u00f3s\u016d voskr\u00e9se! Vo\u00edstinu voskr\u00e9se!)\n**[[Belarusian language|Belarusian]] \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u044b\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0443\u0432\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0440\u043e\u0441! \u0421\u0430\u043f\u0440\u0430\u045e\u0434\u044b \u045e\u0432\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0440\u043e\u0441! (Chrystos uvaskros! Sapra\u016ddy \u016dvaskros!)\n**[[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]] \u2013 ''as if in Church Slavonic'' \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! \u0412\u043e\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0443 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! (Khristos voskrese! Voistinu voskrese!)  ''or in Modern Bulgarian'': \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u044a\u0437\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! \u041d\u0430\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u044a\u0437\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! (Khristos v\u00e2zkrese! Naistina v\u00e2zkrese!) \n**[[Croatian language|Croatian]] \u2013 Krist uskrsnu! Uistinu uskrsnu!\n**[[Czech language|Czech]] \u2013 Kristus vstal z mrtv\u00fdch! Vpravd\u011b vstal z mrtv\u00fdch!\n**[[Macedonian language|Macedonian]]\n*** Traditional (as per Church Slavonic) \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! \u041d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! (Hristos voskrese! Navistina voskrese!)\n*** Vernacular \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0430! \u041d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0430! (Hristos voskresna! Navistina voskresna!)\n**[[Polish language|Polish]] \u2013 Chrystus zmartwychwsta\u0142! Prawdziwie zmartwychwsta\u0142!\n**[[Russian language|Russian]] \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441(-\u0435)! \u0412\u043e\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0443 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441(-\u0435)! (Khristos voskres(-\u0435)! Voistinu voskres(-\u0435)!) (the version with -e is in Church Slavonic, one without it is in modern Russian; both are widely used)\n**[[Rusyn language|Rusyn]] \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u0456\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441! \u0412\u043e\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0443 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441! (Hristos voskres! Voistynu voskres!)\n**[[Serbian language|Serbian]] \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0441\u0435! \u0412\u0430\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0443 \u0432\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0441\u0435! / Hristos vaskrse! Vaistinu vaskrse! ''or'' \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! \u0412\u0430\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0443 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! / Hristos voskrese! Vaistinu voskrese!\n**[[Slovak language|Slovak]] \u2013 Kristus vstal z m\u0155tvych! Skuto\u010dne vstal (z m\u0155tvych)! (although the Church Slavonic version is more often used: Christos voskrese! Voistinu voskrese!)\n**[[Slovenian language|Slovenian]] \u2013 Kristus je vstal! Zares je vstal! \n**[[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]] \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441! \u0412\u043e\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0443 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441! (Khrystos voskres! Voistynu voskres!)\n[[File:Hnizdovsky XrysVos1 Ukr.gif|thumbnail|Ukrainian Easter card]]\n*[[Albanian language|Albanian]] ([[Tosk Albanian|Tosk]]) \u2013 Krishti u ngjall! V\u00ebrtet u ngjall!\n*[[Armenian language|Armenian]] \u2013 \u0554\u0580\u056b\u057d\u057f\u0578\u057d \u0575\u0561\u0580\u0565\u0561\u055c\u0582 \u056b \u0574\u0565\u057c\u0565\u056c\u0578\u0581: \u0555\u0580\u0570\u0576\u0565\u0561\u055c\u056c \u0567 \u0545\u0561\u0580\u0578\u0582\u0569\u056b\u0582\u0576\u0576 \u0554\u0580\u056b\u057d\u057f\u0578\u057d\u056b: (western dialect: Krisdos haryav i merelotz! Orhnyal e Haroutyunen Krisdosi!) \u0554\u0580\u056b\u057d\u057f\u0578\u057d \u0570\u0561\u0580\u0575\u0561\u055c\u057e \u056b \u0574\u0565\u057c\u0565\u056c\u0578\u0581: \u0555\u0580\u0570\u0576\u0575\u0561\u055c\u056c \u0567 \u0540\u0561\u0580\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0576\u0568 \u0554\u0580\u056b\u057d\u057f\u0578\u057d\u056b: (eastern dialect: Khristos haryav i merelotz! Orhnyal e Harouthyoune Khristosi!) \u2013 (Lit: Christ is risen! Blessed is the resurrection of Christ!)\n*[[Germanic languages]]\n**[[Anglic languages]]\n***[[English language|English]] \u2013 \"Christ is risen! Truly, He is risen!\" ''or'' \"Christ is risen! Indeed, He is risen!\" ''or'' \"He [or 'The LORD'] is risen! He [or 'The LORD'] is risen indeed!\" ''or'' \"Christ has risen! Indeed, He has!\" ''or'' \"Christ is risen! He is risen, indeed!\"\n****[[Church of England]] and [[Methodist Church]] \u2013 Alleluia! Christ is Risen! He is risen indeed! Alleluia! <ref>http://www.cofe.anglican.org/worship/downloads/rtf/order_1.rtf {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080829171827/http://www.cofe.anglican.org/worship/downloads/rtf/order_1.rtf |date=2008-08-29 }} \u2013 The Liturgy of the Sacrament (Holy Communion Order One)</ref><ref>The Methodist Worship Book, published by Trustees for Methodist Church Purposes, 1999</ref>\n****[[The Episcopal Church]] \u2013 Alleluia. Christ is Risen. The Lord is risen indeed. Alleluia.<ref>http://www.bcponline.org/HE/he2.htm {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161124124158/http://www.bcponline.org/HE/he2.htm |date=2016-11-24 }} \u2013 The Book of Common Prayer, 1979 (Holy Eucharist Rite II)</ref>\n****[[Old English language|Anglo-Saxon]] \u2013 Crist is \u0101risen! H\u0113 is s\u014d\u00fel\u012b\u010be \u0101risen!\n****[[Middle English language|Middle English]] \u2013 Crist is arisen! Arisen he sothe!\n***[[Iyaric]] \u2013 Krestos a uprisin! Seen, him a uprisin fe tru!\n***[[San Andr\u00e9s\u2013Providencia Creole]] - Christ don riez op! \nIhn don riez op fi chruut!\n***[[Scots language|Scots]] \u2013 Christ has ryssyn! Hech aye, he his ain sel!\n**[[Danish language|Danish]] \u2013 Kristus er opstanden! Sandelig Han er Opstanden!\n**[[West Frisian language|West Frisian]] \u2013 Kristus is opstien! Wis is er opstien!\n**[[German language|German]] \u2013 Christus (or: Der Herr) ist auferstanden! Er ist wahrhaft (or: wahrhaftig) auferstanden!\n**[[Icelandic language|Icelandic]] \u2013 Kristur er upprisinn! Hann er sannarlega upprisinn!\n**[[Faroese language|Faroese]] \u2013 Kristus er upprisin! Hann er sanniliga upprisin!\n**[[Low Franconian languages]]\n***[[Dutch language|Dutch]] \u2013 Christus is opgestaan! Hij is waarlijk opgestaan! ([[Netherlands]]) ''or'' Christus is verrezen! Hij is waarlijk verrezen! ([[Belgium]])\n***[[Afrikaans language|Afrikaans]] \u2013 Christus het opgestaan! Hy het waarlik opgestaan!\n**[[Norwegian language|Norwegian]]\n***[[Bokm\u00e5l|Norwegian Bokm\u00e5l]] \u2013 Kristus er oppstanden! Han er sannelig oppstanden!\n***[[Nynorsk|Norwegian Nynorsk]] \u2013 Kristus er oppstaden! Han er sanneleg oppstaden!\n**[[Swedish language|Swedish]] \u2013 Kristus \u00e4r uppst\u00e5nden! Han \u00e4r sannerligen uppst\u00e5nden!\n*[[Italic languages]]\n**[[Latin]] \u2013 Christus resurrexit! Resurrexit vere!\n**[[Romance languages]]\n***[[Aromanian language|Aromanian]] \u2013 Hristolu anyie! Di alihea anyie!\n***[[Catalan language|Catalan]] \u2013 Crist ha ressuscitat! Veritablement ha ressuscitat!\n***[[French language|French]] \u2013 Le Christ est ressuscit\u00e9 ! En v\u00e9rit\u00e9 il est ressuscit\u00e9 ! ''or'' Le Christ est ressuscit\u00e9 ! Vraiment il est ressuscit\u00e9 !\n***[[Galician language|Galician]] -Cristo resucitou! De verdade resucitou!\n***[[Italian language|Italian]] \u2013 Cristo \u00e8 risorto! \u00c8 veramente risorto!\n***[[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] \u2013 Cristo ressuscitou! Em verdade ressuscitou! ''or'' Cristo ressuscitou! Ressuscitou verdadeiramente!\n***[[Proven\u00e7al language|Proven\u00e7al]] \u2013 Lo Crist es ressuscitat! En veritat es ressuscitat!\n***[[Romanian language|Romanian]] \u2013 Hristos a \u00eenviat! Adev\u0103rat a \u00eenviat!\n***[[Romansh language|Romansh]] \u2013 Cristo es rinaschieu! In varded, el es rinaschieu!\n***[[Sardinian language|Sardinian]] \u2013 Cristu est resuscitadu! Aberu est resuscitadu!\n***[[Sicilian language|Sicilian]] \u2013 Cristu arrivisciutu esti! Pibbiru arrivisciutu esti!\n***[[Spanish language|Spanish]] \u2013 \u00a1Cristo resucit\u00f3! \u00a1En verdad resucit\u00f3!\n***[[Walloon language|Walloon]] \u2013 Li Crist a ravik\u00e9! Il a ravik\u00e9 podbon!\n*[[Baltic languages]]\n**[[Latvian language|Latvian]] \u2013 Kristus (ir) aug\u0161\u0101mc\u0113lies! Patiesi (vi\u0146\u0161 ir) aug\u0161\u0101mc\u0113lies!\n**[[Lithuanian language|Lithuanian]] \u2013 Kristus prisik\u0117l\u0117! Tikrai prisik\u0117l\u0117!\n*[[Celtic languages]]\n**[[Goidelic|Goidelic languages]]\n***[[Goidelic|Old Irish]] \u2013  Asr\u00e9racht Cr\u00edst! Asr\u00e9racht H\u00e9-som co dearb!\n***[[Irish language|Irish]] \u2013 T\u00e1 Cr\u00edost \u00e9irithe! Go deimhin, t\u00e1 s\u00e9 \u00e9irithe!\n***[[Manx language|Manx]] \u2013 Taw Creest Ereen! Taw Shay Ereen Guhdyne!\n***[[Scottish Gaelic language|Scottish]] \u2013 Tha Cr\u00ecosd air \u00e8iridh! Gu dearbh, tha e air \u00e8iridh!\n**[[Brythonic languages]]\n***[[Breton language|Breton]] \u2013 Dassoret eo Krist! E wirionez dassoret eo!\n***[[Cornish language|Cornish]] \u2013 Thew Creest dassorez! En weer thewa dassorez!\n***[[Welsh language|Welsh]] \u2013 Atgyfododd Crist! Yn wir atgyfododd!\n*[[Indo-Iranian languages]]\n**[[Ossetian language|Ossetian]] \u2013 \u0427\u044b\u0440\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u0433\u0430\u0441! \u00c6\u0446\u00e6\u0433\u00e6\u0439 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u0433\u0430\u0441 ''or'' \u0431\u00e6\u043b\u0432\u044b\u0440\u0434 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u0433\u0430\u0441! (\u1e30yrysti rajgas! \u00c6c\u00e6g\u00e6j rajgas or b\u00e6lvyrd rajgas!)\n**[[Persian language|Persian]] \u2013 {{Script/Arabic|\u0645\u0633\u06cc\u062d \u0628\u0631\u062e\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0647 \u0627\u0633\u062a! \u0628\u0647 \u0631\u0627\u0633\u062a\u06cc \u0628\u0631\u062e\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0647 \u0627\u0633\u062a!}} (Masih barkhaste ast! Be rasti barkhaste ast!)\n**[[Hindustani language|Hindustani]] \u2013 \u092f\u0947\u0938\u0941 \u092e\u0938\u0940\u0939 \u091c\u093c\u093f\u0928\u094d\u0926\u093e \u0939\u094b \u0917\u092f\u093e \u0939\u0948! \u0939\u093e\u0901 \u092f\u0915\u093c\u0940\u0928\u0928, \u0935\u094b\u0939 \u091c\u093c\u093f\u0928\u094d\u0926\u093e \u0939\u094b \u0917\u092f\u093e \u0939\u0948! \u2013 {{Script/Nastaliq|\u06cc\u0633\u0648\u0639 \u0645\u0633\u06cc\u062d \u0632\u0646\u062f\u06c1 \u06c1\u0648 \u06af\u06cc\u0627 \u06c1\u06d2! \u06c1\u0627\u06ba \u06cc\u0642\u06cc\u0646\u0627\u064b\u060c \u0648\u06c1 \u0632\u0646\u062f\u06c1 \u06c1\u0648 \u06af\u06cc\u0627 \u06c1\u06d2!}} (Yesu Mas\u012bh zind\u0101 ho gay\u0101 hai! H\u0101\u0303 yaq\u012bnan, voh zind\u0101 ho gay\u0101 hai!)\n**[[Marathi language|Marathi]] \u2013 Yeshu Khrist uthla ahe! Kharokhar uthla ahe!\n\n===[[Afro-Asiatic languages]]===\n*[[Semitic languages]]\n**[[Arabic language|Arabic (standard)]] \u2013 {{Script/Arabic|\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u064a\u062d \u0642\u0627\u0645! \u062d\u0642\u0627 \u0642\u0627\u0645!}} (al-Mas\u012b\u1e25 q\u0101m! \u1e24aqqan q\u0101m!) ''or'' {{Script/Arabic|\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u064a\u062d \u0642\u0627\u0645! \u0628\u0627\u0644\u062d\u0642\u064a\u0642\u0629 \u0642\u0627\u0645!}} (al-Mas\u012b\u1e25 q\u0101m! Bi-l-\u1e25aq\u012bqati q\u0101m!)\n**Aramaic languages\n***[[Syriac language|Syriac]] \u2013 {{rtl-lang|syc|\u0721\u072b\u071d\u071a\u0710 \u0729\u0721! \u072b\u072a\u071d\u072a\u0710\u071d\u072c \u0729\u0721!}} (Mshi\u1e25a q\u0101m! shar\u012br\u0101\u012bth q\u0101m! ''or'' Mshi\u1e25o Qom! Shariroith Qom!)\n***[[Neo-Aramaic languages|Neo-Syriac]] \u2013 {{rtl-lang|syr|\u0721\u072b\u071d\u071a\u0710 \u0729\u0721\u0720\u0717! \u0712\u0717\u0729\u0718\u072c\u0710 \u0729\u0721\u0720\u0717!}} (Mshikha qimlih! bh\u0101qota qimlih!)\n***[[Turoyo|Turoyo-Syriac]] \u2013 {{rtl-lang|syr|\u0721\u072b\u071d\u071a\u0710 \u0729\u071d\u0721! \u072b\u072a\u0725\u072a\u0710\u071d\u072c \u0729\u071d\u0721!}} (Mshi\u1e25o q\u0101yem! Shariroith q\u0101yem!)\n**East African languages\n***[[Tigrigna language|Tigrigna]] \u2013 (Christos tensiou! Bahake tensiou!)\n***[[Amharic language|Amharic]] \u2013 (Kristos Tenestwal! Bergit Tenestwal!)\n**[[Hebrew language|Hebrew (modern)]] \u2013 {{rtl-lang|he|\u05d4\u05de\u05e9\u05d9\u05d7 \u05e7\u05dd! \u05d1\u05d0\u05de\u05ea \u05e7\u05dd!}} (Hameshiach qam! Be'emet qam!)\n**[[Maltese language|Maltese]] \u2013 Kristu qam! Huwa qam tassew! ''or'' Kristu qam mill-mewt! Huwa qam tassew!\n*[[Egyptian language|Egyptian]]\n**[[Coptic language|Coptic (Bohairic)]] \u2013 \u2ca0\u2c93\u2cac\u2ca3\u2c93\u2ca5\u2ca7\u2c9f\u2ca5 \u2c81\u03e5\u2ca7\u2cb1\u2c9b\u03e5! \u03e6\u2c89\u2c9b \u2c9f\u2ca9\u2c99\u2c89\u2c91\u2c99\u2c8f\u2c93 \u2c81\u03e5\u2ca7\u2cb1\u2c9b\u03e5! (Pi'Christos aftonf! Khen oumetmi aftonf!)\n*[[Berber language]] \u2013 (Lmasih yahye-d ger lmeytin! Stidet yahye-d ger lmeytin!)\n\n===[[Kartvelian languages]]===\n*[[Georgian language|Georgian]] \u2013 \u10e5\u10e0\u10d8\u10e1\u10e2\u10d4 \u10d0\u10e6\u10e1\u10d3\u10d2\u10d0! \u10ed\u10d4\u10e8\u10db\u10d0\u10e0\u10d8\u10e2\u10d0\u10d3 \u10d0\u10e6\u10e1\u10d3\u10d2\u10d0! (Kriste aghsdga! Cheshmaritad aghsdga!)\n*[[Mingrelian language|Mengrelian]]  \u10e5\u10d8\u10e0\u10e1\u10d4\u10e5 \u10d2\u10d4\u10d7\u10d0\u10dc\u10d3\u10f7! \u10e6\u10dd\u10e0\u10dd\u10dc\u10d7\u10e3\u10db\u10d4 (\u10d4\u10db\u10d4\u10d7\u10dd \u10d4\u10d7\u10d0\u10dc\u10d3\u10f7)! (Kirsek genthand'! Ghoronthume (emetho gethand')!)\n\n===[[Northwest Caucasian languages]]===\n*[[Abkhazian language|Abkhazian]] \u2013 Kyrsa Dybzaheit! Itzzabyrgny Dybzaheit!\n\n===[[Dravidian languages]]===\n*[[Tamil language|Tamil]] \u2013 \u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b89\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd, \u0bae\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bc7 \u0b85\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b89\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd.\n*[[Malayalam language|Malayalam]] \u2013 \u0d15\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d3f\u0d38\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d41 \u0d09\u0d2f\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d46\u0d34\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d47\u0d31\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d41! \u0d24\u0d40\u0d30\u0d4d\u0d1a\u0d4d\u0d1a\u0d2f\u0d3e\u0d2f\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d09\u0d2f\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d46\u0d34\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d47\u0d31\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d41! (Christu uyirthezhunnettu! Theerchayayum uyirthezhunnettu!)\n\n===[[Eskimo\u2013Aleut languages]]===\n*[[Aleut language|Aleut]] \u2013 Kristusaaq Aglagikuk! Angangulakan Aglagikuk!\n*[[Alutiq language|Alutiq]] \u2013 Kristusaq ungwektaq! Pichinuq ungwektaq!\n*[[Central Alaskan Yup'ik language|Central Alaskan Yup'ik]] \u2013 Kristuussaaq unguirtuq! Ilumun unguirtuq!\n\n===[[Mayan languages]]===\n*[[Tzotzil language|Tzotzil]] \u2013 Icha'kuxi Kajvaltik Kristo! Ta melel icha'kuxi!\n*[[Tzeltal language|Tzeltal]] \u2013 Cha'kuxaj Kajwaltik Kristo! Ta melel cha'kuxaj!\n\n===[[Austronesian languages]]: Malayo-Polynesian ===\n*[[Batak language|Batak]] \u2013 Tuhan nunga hehe! Tutu do ibana hehe!\n*[[Carolinian language|Carolinian]] \u2013 Lios a melau sefal! Meipung, a mahan sefal!\n*[[Cebuano language|Cebuano]] \u2013 Nabanhaw Si Kristo! Nabanhaw gayud!\n*[[Cebuano language|Waray]] \u2013 Hi Kristo nabanwaw! Matuod nga Hiya nabanhaw!\n*[[Chamorro language|Chamorro]] \u2013 La'la'i i Kristo! Magahet na luma'la' i Kristo!\n*[[Fijian language|Fijian]] \u2013 Na Karisito tucake tale! Io sa tucake tale!\n*[[Filipino language|Filipino]] \u2013 Nabuhay muli Si Kristo! Nabuhay talaga!\n*[[Hawaiian language|Hawaiian]] \u2013 Ua ala hou \u02bbo Kristo! Ua ala \u02bbi\u02bbo n\u014d \u02bbo Ia!\n*[[Indonesian language|Indonesian]]/[[Malaysian language|Malaysian]] \u2013 Kristus telah bangkit! Dia benar-benar telah bangkit!\n*[[Kapampangan language|Kapampangan]] \u2013 Y Krist\u00fb sin\u00fbbli y\u00e1ng m\u00e8bi\u00e9! Sin\u00fbbli ya pin m\u00e8bi\u00e9!\n*[[Malagasy language|Malagasy]] \u2013 Nitsangana tamin'ny maty i Kristy! Nitsangana marina tokoa izy!\n*[[Tongan language|Tongan]] -Kuo toetu\u2019u \u2018ae Eiki!\n\u2018Io kuo toetu\u2019u mo\u2019oni!\n\n===[[Austroasiatic languages]]: Mon-Khmer===\n*[[Khmer language|Khmer]] \u2013 Preah Christ mean preah choan rous leong vinh! trung mean preah choan rous leong vinh men!\n\n===[[Vietnamese language|Vietnamese]]===\n* [[Vietnamese language|Vietnamese]] \u2013 Ch\u00faa Ki-t\u00f4 \u0111\u00e3 s\u1ed1ng l\u1ea1i! Ng\u00e0i \u0111\u00e3 s\u1ed1ng l\u1ea1i th\u1eadt!\n\n===[[Thai language|Thai]]===\n* [[Thai language|Thai]] \u2013 \u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e04\u0e23\u0e34\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e4c\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e02\u0e36\u0e49\u0e19\u0e08\u0e32\u0e01\u0e04\u0e27\u0e32\u0e21\u0e15\u0e32\u0e22! ''or'' \u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e04\u0e23\u0e34\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e4c\u0e17\u0e23\u0e07\u0e01\u0e25\u0e31\u0e1a\u0e04\u0e37\u0e19\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e0a\u0e19\u0e21\u0e4c\u0e0a\u0e35\u0e1e!\n\n===[[Basque language|Basque]]===\n* [[Basque language|Basque]] \u2013 Cristo Berbiztua! Benetan Berbiztua!\n\n===[[Japanese language|Japanese]]===\n* [[Japanese language|Japanese]] \u2013 \u30cf\u30ea\u30b9\u30c8\u30b9\u5fa9\u6d3b\uff01\u5b9f\u306b\u5fa9\u6d3b\uff01 (Harisutosu fukkatsu! Jitsu ni fukkatsu!)\n<!--\n[[Japanese language|Japanese]] \u2013 [[Orthodox Church]]: \u30cf\u30ea\u30b9\u30c8\u30b9\u5fa9\u6d3b\uff01\u5b9f\u306b\u5fa9\u6d3b\uff01 (Harisutosu fukkatsu! Jitsu ni fukkatsu!). Other churches: \u30ad\u30ea\u30b9\u30c8\u306f\u5fa9\u6d3b\u3057\u305f\u3001\u771f\u306b\u30ad\u30ea\u30b9\u30c8\u306f\u5fa9\u6d3b\u3057\u305f (Kirisuto wa fukkatsushita, Makotoni fukkatsushita).\n//In general Japanese say \"Christ\" is \"\u30ad\u30ea\u30b9\u30c8/ki-ri-su-to\" (from koine greek) but Orthodox Christian say \"\u30cf\u30ea\u30b9\u30c8\u30b9/ha-ri-su-to-su\" (came from Russian/Church Slavonic). In Japan, general Christianity, this is not general greeting. Because there is very low population ratio of Orthodox Christian per Other Christian.//\n-->\n\n===[[Korean language|Korean]]===\n* [[Korean language|Korean]] \u2013 \uadf8\ub9ac\uc2a4\ub3c4 \ubd80\ud65c\ud558\uc168\ub124! \ucc38\uc73c\ub85c \ubd80\ud65c\ud558\uc168\ub124! (Geuriseudo buhwalhasyeonne! Chameuro buhwalhasyeonne!)\n\n===[[Na-Den\u00e9 languages]]===\n*[[Athabaskan|Athabaskan languages]]\n**[[Navajo language|Navajo]] \u2013 {{spell-nv|Christ daazts\u0105\u0301\u0105\u0301d\u0119\u0301\u0119\u0301\u02bc n\u00e1\u00e1diidz\u00e1\u00e1! T\u02bc\u00e1\u00e1 aan\u00ed\u00ed daazts\u0105\u0301\u0105\u0301d\u0119\u0301\u0119\u0301\u02bc n\u00e1\u00e1diidz\u00e1\u00e1!}}\n*[[Tlingit language|Tlingit]] \u2013 Xristos Kuxwoo-digoot! Xegaa-kux Kuxwoo-digoot!\n\n===[[Niger\u2013Congo languages]]===\n*[[Luganda|Ganda]] \u2013 Kristo Ajukkide! Kweli Ajukkide!\n*[[Swahili language|Swahili]] \u2013 Kristo Amefufuka! Amefufuka kweli kweli!\n*[[Gikuyu language|Gikuyu]] \u2013 Kristo ni muriuku! Ni muriuku nema!\n\n===Quechuan languages===\n*[[Quechua languages|Quechua]] \u2013 Cristo causarimpun\u00f1a! Ciertopuni causarimpun\u00f1a!\n\n===[[Mongolic languages]]===\n*[[Mongolian language|Mongolian]] \u2013 \u0415\u0441\u04af\u0441 \u0434\u0430\u0445\u0438\u043d \u0430\u043c\u0438\u043b\u0441\u0430\u043d, \u0422\u044d\u0440 \u04af\u043d\u044d\u0445\u044d\u044d\u0440 \u0430\u043c\u0438\u043b\u0441\u0430\u043d! (Yesus dahin amilsan, ter uneheer amilsan)\n\n===[[Turkic languages]]===\n*[[Turkish language|Turkish]] \u2013 Mesih dirildi! Hakikaten dirildi!\n*[[Uyghur language|Uyghur]] \u2013 {{ug-textonly|&#x202B;\u0626\u06d5\u064a\u0633\u0627 \u062a\u0649\u0631\u0649\u0644\u062f\u0649! \u06be\u06d5\u0642\u0649\u0642\u06d5\u062a\u0649\u0646\u0644\u0627 \u062a\u0649\u0631\u0649\u0644\u062f\u0649!&#x202C;}} (\u018fysa tirildi! \u2c67\u0259\u2c6ai\u2c6a\u0259tinla tirildi!)\n*[[Azerbaijani language|Azeri]] \u2013 M\u0259sih dirildi! H\u0259qiq\u0259t\u0259n dirildi!\n*[[Chuvash language|Chuvash]] \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0447\u0115\u0440\u0115\u043b\u043d\u0115! \u0427\u0103\u043d \u0447\u0115\u0440\u0115\u043b\u043d\u0115! (Hristos \u010d\u0115r\u0115ln\u0115! \u010cyn \u010d\u0115r\u0115ln\u0115!)\n*[[Khakas language|Khakas]] \u2013 \t\u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0442\u0456\u0440\u0456\u043b\u0434\u0456! \u0421\u044b\u043d\u043d\u0430\u04a3 \u0442\u0456\u0440\u0456\u043b\u0434\u0456! (Hristos t\u00edr\u00edld\u00ed! S\u0131nna\u00f1 t\u00edr\u00edld\u00ed!)\n*[[Uzbek language|Uzbek]] \u2013 \u041c\u0430\u0441\u0438\u0445 \u0442\u0438\u0440\u0438\u043b\u0434\u0438! \u0425\u0430\u049b\u0438\u049b\u0430\u0442\u0434\u0430\u043d \u0442\u0438\u0440\u0438\u043b\u0434\u0438! (Masih tirildi! Haqiqatdan tirildi!)\n\n===[[Sino-Tibetan languages]]===\n*[[Mandarin Chinese|Mandarin]] \u2013 \u57fa\u7763\u5fa9\u6d3b\u4e86\uff01\u4ed6\u78ba\u5be6\u5fa9\u6d3b\u4e86\uff01(J\u012bd\u016b f\u00f9hu\u00f3-le! T\u0101 qu\u00e8sh\u00ed f\u00f9hu\u00f3-le!) ''or'' \u8036\u7a4c\u5fa9\u6d3b\u4e86\uff0c\u771f\u7684\u4ed6\u5fa9\u6d3b\u4e86\uff01(Y\u0113s\u016b f\u00f9hu\u00f3-le, Zh\u0113nde t\u0101 f\u00f9hu\u00f3-le!)\n\n===[[Uralic languages]]===\n*[[Estonian language|Estonian]] \u2013 Kristus on \u00fcles t\u00f5usnud! T\u00f5esti on \u00fcles t\u00f5usnud!\n*[[Finnish language|Finnish]] \u2013 Kristus nousi kuolleista! Totisesti nousi!\n*[[Hungarian language|Hungarian]] \u2013 Krisztus felt\u00e1madt! Val\u00f3ban felt\u00e1madt!\n*[[Karelian language|Karelian]] \u2013 Hristos nouzi kuollielois! Tovessah nouzi!\n\n===[[Constructed language]]s===\n*[[International auxiliary language]]s\n**[[Esperanto]] \u2013 Kristo levi\u011dis! Vere Li levi\u011dis!\n**[[Ido (language)|Ido]] \u2013 Kristo riviveskabas! Ya Il rivivesakabas!\n**[[Interlingua]] \u2013 Christo ha resurgite! Vermente ille ha resurgite! ''or'' Christo ha resurrecte! Vermente ille ha resurrecte!\n*[[Quenya]] \u2013 [[Image:Quenya Paschal Greeting.png|Tengwar Rendering]] (Hristo Ortane! Anwave Ortanes!)\n*[[Klingon language|Klingon]] \u2013 Hu'ta' QISt! Hu'bejta'!\n*[[Toki Pona]] \u2013 jan sewi Kolisu li tawa tan moli! ni li lon: ona li tawa tan moli!\n*[[Dothraki language|Dothraki]] \u2013 Khal Asvezhvenanaz yathoay! Me Yathoay Me nem nesa!\n*[[The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim|Dovahzul]] \u2013 Saviik los alok! Rok los vahzah alok!\n\n==References==\n* [http://oca.org/orthodoxy/paschal-greetings Paschal Greetings from Around the World], [[Orthodox Church in America]] website.\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130403014524/http://www.stjohndc.org/Russian/feasts/FeastsE/e_pascha_greeting07.htm The Origin and Meaning of the Paschal Greeting], Russian Orthodox Cathedral of St. John the Baptist, Washington, DC.\n* [http://srbigham.com/en/ The Paschal Greeting said in 250 languages] on Pascha Polyglotta\n* [http://orthodoxwiki.org/Paschal_greeting Paschal Greeting article on Orthodox Wiki]\n{{Easter}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List of translations of the Paschal Greeting}}\n[[Category:Eastern Orthodox liturgy]]\n[[Category:Language comparison]]\n[[Category:Easter liturgy]]\n[[Category:Christian terminology]]\n[[Category:Greeting words and phrases]]\n", "text_old": "{{cleanup lang|date=May 2019}}\n[[File:Resurrection_(24).jpg|right|thumb|The [[w: Resurrection of Jesus Christ|resurrection of Jesus Christ]] from the [[dead]], described in the [[New Testament]] as having occurred on the third day after [[Crucifixion of Jesus|his crucifixion]] at [[Calvary]].]]\n{{Eastern Orthodox sidebar|expanded=worship}}\nThis article lists translations of the Christian [[Paschal greeting]] in various languages.\n\n==The Paschal Greeting in various languages==\n\n===[[Indo-European languages]]===\n*[[Greek language|Greek]] \u2013 \u03a7\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u1f78\u03c2 \u1f00\u03bd\u03ad\u03c3\u03c4\u03b7! \u1f08\u03bb\u03b7\u03b8\u1ff6\u03c2 \u1f00\u03bd\u03ad\u03c3\u03c4\u03b7! (Khrist\u00f3s An\u00e9sti! Alith\u00f3s An\u00e9sti!)\n*[[Slavic languages]]\n**[[Church Slavonic language|Church Slavonic]] \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u0457\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0301\u0441\u044a \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0301\u0441\u0435! \u0412\u043e\u0438\u0301\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\ua64b \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0301\u0441\u0435! (Xrist\u00f3s\u016d voskr\u00e9se! Vo\u00edstinu voskr\u00e9se!)\n**[[Belarusian language|Belarusian]] \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u044b\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0443\u0432\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0440\u043e\u0441! \u0421\u0430\u043f\u0440\u0430\u045e\u0434\u044b \u045e\u0432\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0440\u043e\u0441! (Chrystos uvaskros! Sapra\u016ddy \u016dvaskros!)\n**[[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]] \u2013 ''as if in Church Slavonic'' \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! \u0412\u043e\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0443 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! (Khristos voskrese! Voistinu voskrese!)  ''or in Modern Bulgarian'': \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u044a\u0437\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! \u041d\u0430\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u044a\u0437\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! (Khristos v\u00e2zkrese! Naistina v\u00e2zkrese!) \n**[[Croatian language|Croatian]] \u2013 Krist uskrsnu! Uistinu uskrsnu!\n**[[Czech language|Czech]] \u2013 Kristus vstal z mrtv\u00fdch! Vpravd\u011b vstal z mrtv\u00fdch!\n**[[Macedonian language|Macedonian]]\n*** Traditional (as per Church Slavonic) \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! \u041d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! (Hristos voskrese! Navistina voskrese!)\n*** Vernacular \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0430! \u041d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0430! (Hristos voskresna! Navistina voskresna!)\n**[[Polish language|Polish]] \u2013 Chrystus zmartwychwsta\u0142! Prawdziwie zmartwychwsta\u0142!\n**[[Russian language|Russian]] \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441(-\u0435)! \u0412\u043e\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0443 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441(-\u0435)! (Khristos voskres(-\u0435)! Voistinu voskres(-\u0435)!) (the version with -e is in Church Slavonic, one without it is in modern Russian; both are widely used)\n**[[Rusyn language|Rusyn]] \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u0456\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441! \u0412\u043e\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0443 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441! (Hristos voskres! Voistynu voskres!)\n**[[Serbian language|Serbian]] \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0441\u0435! \u0412\u0430\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0443 \u0432\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0441\u0435! / Hristos vaskrse! Vaistinu vaskrse! ''or'' \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! \u0412\u0430\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0443 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435! / Hristos voskrese! Vaistinu voskrese!\n**[[Slovak language|Slovak]] \u2013 Kristus vstal z m\u0155tvych! Skuto\u010dne vstal (z m\u0155tvych)! (although the Church Slavonic version is more often used: Christos voskrese! Voistinu voskrese!)\n**[[Slovenian language|Slovenian]] \u2013 Kristus je vstal! Zares je vstal! \n**[[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]] \u2013 \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441! \u0412\u043e\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0443 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0440\u0435\u0441! (Khrystos voskres! Voistynu voskres!)\n[[File:Hnizdovsky XrysVos1 Ukr.gif|thumbnail|Ukrainian Easter card]]\n*[[Albanian language|Albanian]] ([[Tosk Albanian|Tosk]]) \u2013 Krishti u ngjall! V\u00ebrtet u ngjall!\n*[[Armenian language|Armenian]] \u2013 \u0554\u0580\u056b\u057d\u057f\u0578\u057d \u0575\u0561\u0580\u0565\u0561\u055c\u0582 \u056b \u0574\u0565\u057c\u0565\u056c\u0578\u0581: \u0555\u0580\u0570\u0576\u0565\u0561\u055c\u056c \u0567 \u0545\u0561\u0580\u0578\u0582\u0569\u056b\u0582\u0576\u0576 \u0554\u0580\u056b\u057d\u057f\u0578\u057d\u056b: (western dialect: Krisdos haryav i merelotz! Orhnyal e Haroutyunen Krisdosi!) \u0554\u0580\u056b\u057d\u057f\u0578\u057d \u0570\u0561\u0580\u0575\u0561\u055c\u057e \u056b \u0574\u0565\u057c\u0565\u056c\u0578\u0581: \u0555\u0580\u0570\u0576\u0575\u0561\u055c\u056c \u0567 \u0540\u0561\u0580\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0576\u0568 \u0554\u0580\u056b\u057d\u057f\u0578\u057d\u056b: (eastern dialect: Khristos haryav i merelotz! Orhnyal e Harouthyoune Khristosi!) \u2013 (Lit: Christ is risen! Blessed is the resurrection of Christ!)\n*[[Germanic languages]]\n**[[Anglic languages]]\n***[[English language|English]] \u2013 \"Christ is risen! Truly, He is risen!\" ''or'' \"Christ is risen! Indeed, He is risen!\" ''or'' \"He [or 'The LORD'] is risen! He [or 'The LORD'] is risen indeed!\" ''or'' \"Christ has risen! Indeed, He has!\" ''or'' \"Christ is risen! He is risen, indeed!\"\n****[[Church of England]] and [[Methodist Church]] \u2013 Alleluia! Christ is Risen! He is risen indeed! Alleluia! <ref>http://www.cofe.anglican.org/worship/downloads/rtf/order_1.rtf {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080829171827/http://www.cofe.anglican.org/worship/downloads/rtf/order_1.rtf |date=2008-08-29 }} \u2013 The Liturgy of the Sacrament (Holy Communion Order One)</ref><ref>The Methodist Worship Book, published by Trustees for Methodist Church Purposes, 1999</ref>\n****[[The Episcopal Church]] \u2013 Alleluia. Christ is Risen. The Lord is risen indeed. Alleluia.<ref>http://www.bcponline.org/HE/he2.htm {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161124124158/http://www.bcponline.org/HE/he2.htm |date=2016-11-24 }} \u2013 The Book of Common Prayer, 1979 (Holy Eucharist Rite II)</ref>\n****[[Old English language|Anglo-Saxon]] \u2013 Crist is \u0101risen! H\u0113 is s\u014d\u00fel\u012b\u010be \u0101risen!\n****[[Middle English language|Middle English]] \u2013 Crist is arisen! Arisen he sothe!\n***[[Iyaric]] \u2013 Krestos a uprisin! Seen, him a uprisin fe tru!\n***[[Scots language|Scots]] \u2013 Christ has ryssyn! Hech aye, he his ain sel!\n**[[Danish language|Danish]] \u2013 Kristus er opstanden! Sandelig Han er Opstanden!\n**[[West Frisian language|West Frisian]] \u2013 Kristus is opstien! Wis is er opstien!\n**[[German language|German]] \u2013 Christus (or: Der Herr) ist auferstanden! Er ist wahrhaft (or: wahrhaftig) auferstanden!\n**[[Icelandic language|Icelandic]] \u2013 Kristur er upprisinn! Hann er sannarlega upprisinn!\n**[[Faroese language|Faroese]] \u2013 Kristus er upprisin! Hann er sanniliga upprisin!\n**[[Low Franconian languages]]\n***[[Dutch language|Dutch]] \u2013 Christus is opgestaan! Hij is waarlijk opgestaan! ([[Netherlands]]) ''or'' Christus is verrezen! Hij is waarlijk verrezen! ([[Belgium]])\n***[[Afrikaans language|Afrikaans]] \u2013 Christus het opgestaan! Hy het waarlik opgestaan!\n**[[Norwegian language|Norwegian]]\n***[[Bokm\u00e5l|Norwegian Bokm\u00e5l]] \u2013 Kristus er oppstanden! Han er sannelig oppstanden!\n***[[Nynorsk|Norwegian Nynorsk]] \u2013 Kristus er oppstaden! Han er sanneleg oppstaden!\n**[[Swedish language|Swedish]] \u2013 Kristus \u00e4r uppst\u00e5nden! Han \u00e4r sannerligen uppst\u00e5nden!\n*[[Italic languages]]\n**[[Latin]] \u2013 Christus resurrexit! Resurrexit vere!\n**[[Romance languages]]\n***[[Aromanian language|Aromanian]] \u2013 Hristolu anyie! Di alihea anyie!\n***[[Catalan language|Catalan]] \u2013 Crist ha ressuscitat! Veritablement ha ressuscitat!\n***[[French language|French]] \u2013 Le Christ est ressuscit\u00e9 ! En v\u00e9rit\u00e9 il est ressuscit\u00e9 ! ''or'' Le Christ est ressuscit\u00e9 ! Vraiment il est ressuscit\u00e9 !\n***[[Galician language|Galician]] -Cristo resucitou! De verdade resucitou!\n***[[Italian language|Italian]] \u2013 Cristo \u00e8 risorto! \u00c8 veramente risorto!\n***[[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] \u2013 Cristo ressuscitou! Em verdade ressuscitou! ''or'' Cristo ressuscitou! Ressuscitou verdadeiramente!\n***[[Proven\u00e7al language|Proven\u00e7al]] \u2013 Lo Crist es ressuscitat! En veritat es ressuscitat!\n***[[Romanian language|Romanian]] \u2013 Hristos a \u00eenviat! Adev\u0103rat a \u00eenviat!\n***[[Romansh language|Romansh]] \u2013 Cristo es rinaschieu! In varded, el es rinaschieu!\n***[[Sardinian language|Sardinian]] \u2013 Cristu est resuscitadu! Aberu est resuscitadu!\n***[[Sicilian language|Sicilian]] \u2013 Cristu arrivisciutu esti! Pibbiru arrivisciutu esti!\n***[[Spanish language|Spanish]] \u2013 \u00a1Cristo resucit\u00f3! \u00a1En verdad resucit\u00f3!\n***[[Walloon language|Walloon]] \u2013 Li Crist a ravik\u00e9! Il a ravik\u00e9 podbon!\n*[[Baltic languages]]\n**[[Latvian language|Latvian]] \u2013 Kristus (ir) aug\u0161\u0101mc\u0113lies! Patiesi (vi\u0146\u0161 ir) aug\u0161\u0101mc\u0113lies!\n**[[Lithuanian language|Lithuanian]] \u2013 Kristus prisik\u0117l\u0117! Tikrai prisik\u0117l\u0117!\n*[[Celtic languages]]\n**[[Goidelic|Goidelic languages]]\n***[[Goidelic|Old Irish]] \u2013  Asr\u00e9racht Cr\u00edst! Asr\u00e9racht H\u00e9-som co dearb!\n***[[Irish language|Irish]] \u2013 T\u00e1 Cr\u00edost \u00e9irithe! Go deimhin, t\u00e1 s\u00e9 \u00e9irithe!\n***[[Manx language|Manx]] \u2013 Taw Creest Ereen! Taw Shay Ereen Guhdyne!\n***[[Scottish Gaelic language|Scottish]] \u2013 Tha Cr\u00ecosd air \u00e8iridh! Gu dearbh, tha e air \u00e8iridh!\n**[[Brythonic languages]]\n***[[Breton language|Breton]] \u2013 Dassoret eo Krist! E wirionez dassoret eo!\n***[[Cornish language|Cornish]] \u2013 Thew Creest dassorez! En weer thewa dassorez!\n***[[Welsh language|Welsh]] \u2013 Atgyfododd Crist! Yn wir atgyfododd!\n*[[Indo-Iranian languages]]\n**[[Ossetian language|Ossetian]] \u2013 \u0427\u044b\u0440\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u0433\u0430\u0441! \u00c6\u0446\u00e6\u0433\u00e6\u0439 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u0433\u0430\u0441 ''or'' \u0431\u00e6\u043b\u0432\u044b\u0440\u0434 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u0433\u0430\u0441! (\u1e30yrysti rajgas! \u00c6c\u00e6g\u00e6j rajgas or b\u00e6lvyrd rajgas!)\n**[[Persian language|Persian]] \u2013 {{Script/Arabic|\u0645\u0633\u06cc\u062d \u0628\u0631\u062e\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0647 \u0627\u0633\u062a! \u0628\u0647 \